@EnvAgencyAnglia @AnglianWater Hello can I ask why the river nene is allowed to flood every year going through kingsthorpe Mill restricting businesses and wildlife from being able to have there land without it being underwater 
Please can something be done ??
@BBCNorthampton

@shandy_defender @EnvAgencyYNE Yes - @RotherValley.

In a flood we lift the gate &amp; it stores water into two lakes, then finally into the main lake (all formally designated reservoirs).

It stores 1,500,000 m3 (cubic meters) of water and operates as a trio with Woodhouse and Canklow storing 3.4million m3 https://t.co/JXIv5khrsQ
